The paper deals with the computation of the 2-adic complexity of binary sequences, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the investigation of optimal autocorrelation sequences, which is a topic related to discrete structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents a new method for computing linear complexity, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI).
